section.section:
The lender is not required to issue a receipt if, before the due date of each payment, he regularly delivers to the borrower a billing statement which specifies:
The previous unpaid principal balance of the loan;
The amount and date of each payment made during the billing period;
The amount of each of these payments applied to interest;
The amount of each of these payments applied to principal;
The current unpaid principal balance; and
The amount and due date of the next maturing installment.
